  "text": "For laser confocal microscopy, a Leica TCS SP was used. Optical sections ranged from 0.2 to 1.5 µm, recorded in line average mode with a picture size of 512 × 512 pixels or 1024 × 1024 pixels. Captured images from optical sections were arranged and processed using Leica confocal Software (LCS). Complete series of optical sections were imported and processed using ImageJ. Generation of three-dimensional digital models and raw tiff stacks (stacks of optical sections) were done using AMIRA (Mercury Computer Systems) as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
